{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Darumaka}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|prevnum=553|prev=Krookodile|nextnum=555|next=Darmanitan|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Darumaka\n|jname=ダルマッカ\n|tmname=Darumakka\n|category=Zen Charm\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Fire\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Hustle\n|abilityd=Inner Focus\n|ndex=554\n|udex=060\n|u2dex=102\n|height-ftin=2\'00"\n|height-m=0.6\n|weight-lbs=82.7\n|weight-kg=37.5\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=20\n|expyield=63\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Red\n|catchrate=120\n|evtotal=1\n|evat=1\n|body=12\n|pokefordex=darumaka\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Darumaka\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ダルマッカ\'\'\' \'\'Darumakka\'\') is a {{type|Fire}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Darmanitan}} starting at [[level]] 35.\n\nIn [[Galar]], Darumaka has a [[regional variant]] that is {{t|Ice}}. It evolves into {{glr|Darmanitan}}.\n\n==Biology==\n[[File:Darumaka sleeping.png|thumb|left|240px|Darumaka asleep]]\nDarumaka is a round, red Pokémon with an orange face and yellow curly eyebrows. It has three yellow ovals on its abdomen and a curvy yellow line on its back. Its paws are orange and have three digits each. It has very warm droppings, which ancient people put in their clothes to keep themselves warm.\n\nWhen the flame inside its body burns, Darumaka is very active. It cannot calm down in this state, and thus becomes uncontrollable. As the flame shrinks, it falls asleep. It can tuck in its arms and legs when it rests; during that time, it slightly sways. While it is sleeping, it cannot be tipped over no matter how much it is pushed or pulled, like a {{wp|Tumbler toy|tumbler doll}}, which it resembles in this state. It prefers to live in a desert environment.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Darumaka anime.png|thumb|left|250px|Darumaka in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nTwo Darumaka debuted in \'\'[[BW008|Saving Darmanitan From the Bell!]]\'\', where they were stealing food for a {{p|Darmanitan}} who couldn\'t move because it was in {{a|Zen Mode}} during an effort to keep a [[clock tower]] from collapsing with its {{m|Psychic}}. They reappeared in a flashback in \'\'[[BW064|Explorers of the Hero\'s Ruin!]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn2|wild}} Darumaka appeared in [[PK22]] alongside a {{p|Drilbur}} and {{p|Gothita}}. All three were angry at {{AP|Oshawott}} and {{AP|Tepig}}, who had eaten the apples that they had collected.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[BW105|Lost at the League!]]\'\', where it battled [[Ash\'s Scraggy]] during the [[Vertress Conference]] and was defeated.\n\nThree Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[BW129|The Pirates of Decolore!]]\'\', under the ownership of two young Trainers. They were trapped on a stranded inflatable raft, but were eventually rescued by the pirate Pokémon.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Trainer\'s Darumaka appeared in {{an|Iris}}\'s flashback in \'\'[[BW033|Iris and Excadrill Against the Dragon Buster!]]\'\'.\n\nA Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[BW041|The Club Battle Hearts of Fury: Emolga Versus Sawk!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Dino]]. He used it against {{Ash}} and his {{AP|Palpitoad}} in the semifinals of the [[Club Battle]] Tournament, but it was defeated by one {{m|Hydro Pump}}. It was revealed to have evolved into Darmanitan during \'\'[[BW108|A Unova League Evolution!]]\'\'.\n\nA Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[BW055|Scraggy and the Demanding Gothita!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Katharine]]. It was offered to Ash for a [[trade]] for his {{AP|Scraggy}}.\n\nMultiple Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[BW056|The Lonely Deino!]]\'\', under the care of a {{pkmn|Day Care}} owner named [[Bobby]].\n\nMultiple Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[BW057|The Mighty Accelguard to the Rescue!]]\'\'.\n\nA Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[BW059|Stopping the Rage of Legends! Part 1]]\'\'. Multiple Darumaka appeared in [[BW060|the follow-up episode]].\n\nTwo Darumaka appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[BW064|Explorers of the Hero\'s Ruin!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Darumaka made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[BW067|Cilan Takes Flight!]]\'\', during a flashback.\n\nA Trainer\'s Darumaka made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[BW069|Climbing the Tower of Success!]]\'\'.\n\nA Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[M15|Kyurem VS. The Sword of Justice]]\'\' during the {{OBP|Swords of Justice|M15}} legend.\n\nA Darumaka appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[BW118|Secrets From Out of the Fog!]]\'\'.\n\nA Darumaka appeared in a fantasy in \'\'[[BW120|Ash and N: A Clash of Ideals!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[BW127|The Island of Illusions!]]\'\' as residents of [[Grand Spectrala Islet]].\n\nA Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[BW134|The Journalist from Another Region!]]\'\', under the ownership of a girl.\n\nThree Trainers\' Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[SM034|A Crowning Moment of Truth!]]\'\'. They were among the Pokémon attending the [[Wela Fire Festival\u200e]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW008|Darumaka|Ash\'s Pokédex|Darumaka, the Zen Charm Pokémon. When asleep, even when pushed or pulled, it cannot be knocked over.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Socialite Blitzle Clerk Darumaka.png|thumb|150px|Darumaka in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pocket Monsters BW: The Heroes of Fire and Thunder manga===\nA Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[FAT4|Get the Legendary Pokémon!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nDarumaka debuted in \'\'[[PS466|An Odd Speech]]\'\', under the ownership of a female {{tc|Office Worker|Clerk}} listening to [[Ghetsis]]\'s speech in [[Accumula Town]].\n\nA Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[PS479|The Case of the Missing Pokémon]]\'\', where it was one of the Pokémon kidnapped by [[Team Plasma]]. It was later returned to its {{pkmn|Trainer}} after being found in a stronghold.\n\nA Darumaka was among several Pokémon attracted to [[Alder]]\'s wrestling match with his {{p|Bouffalant}} in [[Nimbasa City]] in \'\'[[PS487|A New Perspective]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[PS535|Angry Boy]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[PS536|Cold Storage Battle]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon + Nobunaga\'s Ambition ~ Ranse\'s Color Picture Scroll ~ manga===\nA Darumaka appeared in \'\'[[PNA1|The White Scroll: Oichi\'s Worries]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Darumaka (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Fire}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=060|label1={{gameabbrev5|BW}}:|reg2=Unova|num2=102|label2={{gameabbrev5|B2W2}}:}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Black|t=FFF|entry=When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=White|entry=Darumaka\'s droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to {{tt|1,100°F|600°C}}.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=Darumaka\'s droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=Darumaka\'s droppings are hot, so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=Fire}}\n{{Availab